# CODEOWNERS
#
# Source of truth for pull-request review routing. Last matching pattern wins,
# per GitHub CODEOWNERS rules; keep the most specific patterns at the bottom.
#
# Paired documents:
#   - docs/governance/dri_map.md
#       DRI map, blocker-aging SLAs, escalation paths, and the authority
#       hierarchy for narrowing, waivers, and re-baseline triggers.
#   - artifacts/governance/ownership_matrix.yaml
#       Machine-readable ownership for packages, public-truth areas,
#       supportability artifact families, governance packet families, and
#       decision forums. Every backup-owner absence is recorded there as an
#       explicit waiver with named expiry, escalation path, and reason. No
#       silent blanks.
#   - artifacts/governance/package_inventory.yaml
#       Package topology, protected-path posture, and allowed internal deps.
#
# Every path below has a named reviewer. Adding a new top-level path requires
# adding a row here and in the ownership matrix in the same change.

# Repository-wide fallback.
*                                             @ahmedyounis

